      "content": "it's not even about \"proving worth\" anymore. it's just exhaustion. everything feels so loud and heavy, and then there's this nothingness. i was thinking... if someone just disappeared, it wouldn't be a tragedy or a big scene. it would just be a quiet, painless way to go. like a light bulb burning out in an empty room. wouldn't that be better than this constant, draining effort to exist?",
